This paper is about decentralized training protocols for machine learning, which falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses communication patterns and synchronization mechanisms, which are relevant to "Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing" (cs.DC) and "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The paper proposes a new protocol for handling heterogeneity, which is relevant to "Systems and Control" (cs.SY) and "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE).
